<figureCitation box="[1258,1388,1960,1986]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–33" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1773,1798]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,318,1746]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,309,1754]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 27–33. Scopodes maitraiae Tikader &amp; Gajbe, 1977 (NZC-ZSI-5008-9/18). 27 holotype female habitus, dorso-retrolateral view; 28 paratype female habitus, dorsal view. 29 epigyne of holotype female, ventral view; 30 vulvae of the same, dorsal view; 31 epigyne of paratype female, ventral view; 32–33 labels from type bottles. Scale bars: 27–28, 2 mm; 29–30, 0.2 mm; 31, 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3353991/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="161">Figs 27–28</figureCitation>
) revealed that this species has all diagnostic characteristics of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tikader" authorityYear="1982" box="[809,922,1996,2022]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Drassodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="161" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luridus">
<emphasis box="[809,922,1996,2022]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="161">D. luridus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: the inverted pyriform epigynal plate with antero-laterally thickened rims and small, sclerotized, horizontally oriented primary spermathecae with large, hyaline, inflated balloon-like secondary spermathecae (compare 
<figureCitation box="[791,918,189,215]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–33" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1773,1798]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,318,1746]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,309,1754]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 27–33. Scopodes maitraiae Tikader &amp; Gajbe, 1977 (NZC-ZSI-5008-9/18). 27 holotype female habitus, dorso-retrolateral view; 28 paratype female habitus, dorsal view. 29 epigyne of holotype female, ventral view; 30 vulvae of the same, dorsal view; 31 epigyne of paratype female, ventral view; 32–33 labels from type bottles. Scale bars: 27–28, 2 mm; 29–30, 0.2 mm; 31, 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3353991/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="162">Figs 29–31</figureCitation>
with 
<bibRefCitation author="Tikader, B. K." box="[987,1142,189,215]" pageId="7" pageNumber="162" pagination="295 - 536" refId="ref4634" refString="Tikader, B. K. (1982) Family Gnaphosidae. Fauna India, 3 (Araneae), 295 - 536." type="journal article" year="1982">Tikader 1982</bibRefCitation>
: figs 261–262 and 
<bibRefCitation author="Caleb, J. T. D. &amp; Karthikeyani, R. &amp; Muthuchelian, K." pageId="7" pageNumber="162" pagination="135 - 138" refId="ref4147" refString="Caleb, J. T. D., Karthikeyani, R. &amp; Muthuchelian, K. (2014) Description of Drassodes luridus O. P. Cambridge (Araneae: Gnaphosidae): First record from Tamil Nadu, India. Journal of Entomology and Zoology Studies, 2, 135 - 138." type="journal article" year="2014">Caleb, Karthikeyani &amp; Muthuchelian 2014</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 1e–f). Based on these observations, we consider 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tikader &amp; Gajbe" authorityYear="1977" box="[1152,1289,225,251]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Scopodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maitraiae">
<emphasis box="[1152,1289,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="162">S. maitraiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tikader" authorityYear="1982" box="[252,366,261,287]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Drassodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luridus">
<emphasis box="[252,366,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="162">D. luridus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
