<emphasis box="[349,539,1773,1797]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="163">
<taxonomicName box="[349,445,1773,1797]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Scopodes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="163" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Scopodes</taxonomicName>
maitraia
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
e 
<bibRefCitation author="Tikader, B. K. &amp; Gajbe, U. A." box="[558,796,1773,1798]" pageId="8" pageNumber="163" pagination="13 - 22" refId="ref4658" refString="Tikader, B. K. &amp; Gajbe, U. A. (1977) Studies on some spiders of the genera Scopodes Chamberlin, Megamyrmecion Reuss, Scotophaeus Simon and Liodrassus Chamberlin (family: Gnaphosidae) from India. Records of the Zoological Survey of India, 73, 13 - 22." type="journal article" year="1977">Tikader &amp; Gajbe, 1977</bibRefCitation>
(NZC-ZSI-5008-9/18). 27 holotype female habitus, dorso-retrolateral view; 28 paratype female habitus, dorsal view. 29 epigyne of holotype female, ventral view; 30 vulvae of the same, dorsal view; 31 epigyne of paratype female, ventral view; 32–33 labels from type bottles. Scale bars: 27–28, 2 mm; 29–30, 0.2 mm; 31, 0.5 mm.
</paragraph>
